Super speedy, this Easy Peasy Gochujang Beef Udon takes only 15 minutes to make. The popular Korean condiment gochujang contains chillies, fermented soybeans and glutinous rice which give it its savoury-sweet flavour.

> HIGH PROTEIN - Protein contributes to the maintenance of muscle mass.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%grams} and @sliced mushrooms{80%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt and @pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the @sliced spring greens{150%grams} and garlic to the frying pan.

Stir-fry, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next, stir in the @gochujang paste{50%grams}, @soy sauce{25%milliliters}, @water{50%milliliters} and @honey{1%tbsp} (see pantry for both). Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%grams} to the pan. Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to gently separate them. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if the sauce is too thick.

Share the noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle with @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!